==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expenditure
<hw>Ex*pend"iture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of expending; a laying out, as of money; disbursement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>expenditure</qex> purchased commerce and conquest.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is expended or paid out;
expense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The receipts and <qex>expenditures</qex> of this extensive
country.</q> <rj><qau>A. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expense</ent>⟦br⟧
